maml:description.maml:para: Send data to a importhandler configured in Easit BPS / Easit GO.

**This command is considered deprecated as of the release of version 3 of the module EasitGoWebservice.
This command will not get any new functionality and is used as a proxy for Import-GOItem. Please use Import-GOItem instead.**

Update or create an asset in Easit BPS / Easit GO. Specify 'ID' to update an existing asset.
This command used SOAP/XML and Invoke-WebRequest to communicate with the web service in BPS / GO.
API-key for Easit BPS / Easit GO.
Contract start date for asset. Format = yyyy-MM-dd
ID of organization to be set as supplier of asset.
Full path to file to be included in payload.
Path to directory where the configuration file for the web service is.

If specified, payload will be save as payload_1.xml (or next available number) to your desktop instead of sent to Easit BPS / Easit GO. This parameter does not append, rewrite or remove any files from your desktop.
ID for asset in Easit BPS / Easit GO.
Last inventory date of asset. Format = yyyy-MM-dd
ID of contact to be set as owner of asset.
ID of organization to be set as owner of asset.
ID of price list to connect with asset.
Date of purchase of asset. Format = yyyy-MM-dd
Notes about when service is undergoing maintenance.
Service level agreement of asset. Valid values = true / false.
Expire date for SLA of asset. Format: yyyy-MM-dd

Used if system is using SSO with IWA (Active Directory). Not needed when using SSO with SAML2.
Cmdlet will use the credentials of the current user to send the web request.
Unique ID for object during import.
URL to Easit BPS / Easit GO web service.
This parameter is required when Internet Explorer is not installed on the computers, such as on a Server Core installation of a Windows Server operating system.
Date for when warranty of asset expires. Format = yyyy-MM-dd
